; Regression test for issue #590: Budget entry is applied only once if xacts are in reverse order (BZ#590)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/590
;
; When transactions are in reverse chronological order (newer dates first),
; the budget should still apply one entry per period. Instead, only one
; budget entry is generated regardless of how many periods are covered.
;
; Forward order (correct): two budget entries (Jan + Feb) are produced.
; Reverse order (broken):  only one budget entry (Feb) is produced.

~ Monthly
    Expenses:Food    $500.00
    Assets:Cash

2012/02/10 Groceries
    Expenses:Food    $200.00
    Assets:Cash

2012/01/15 Groceries
    Expenses:Food    $100.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg --budget -b 2012/01 -e 2012/03 Expenses
12-Feb-01 Budget transaction    Expenses:Food              $-500.00     $-500.00
12-Feb-10 Groceries             Expenses:Food               $200.00     $-300.00
12-Jan-15 Groceries             Expenses:Food               $100.00     $-200.00
end test
